This paper discusses the security and privacy concerns related to personal data processing and proposes a new approach called the Trusted Server. The paper focuses on cryptographic techniques and secure computing environments, which are typically discussed in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of system administrators on privacy, which is related to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses distributed computing and data obfuscation technologies, which are related to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses legal and ethical requirements related to personal data processing, which is related to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category.
